  "prompt": "What consumer startups have real technology?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, several consumer startups are recognized for their innovative technologies and real-world applications. Here are a few notable examples:\n\n1. **Oura Ring** - A sleep and activity tracker that offers insights into health metrics through a high-tech, stylish ring. It uses advanced sensors to monitor heart rate, body temperature, and sleep stages.\n\n2. **Peloton** - A fitness platform that combines high-quality exercise equipment with an interactive app offering live and on-demand classes. The technology includes a large touchscreen for streaming workouts and high-fidelity audio.\n\n3. **Raspberry Pi** - While not a traditional \"startup,\" the foundation behind Raspberry Pi has spurred a multitude of consumer products focused on education and DIY tech projects, allowing users to build their own computing solutions.\n\n4. **Superpedestrian** - Known for its high-tech e-scooters, Superpedestrian developed smart mobility solutions that include built-in technology for energy efficiency and rider safety.\n\n5. **Tonal** - A smart home gym that uses digital weights and advanced machine learning algorithms to provide personalized workouts. Its technology tracks user performance and adjusts resistance in real-time.\n\n6. **Lime** - A scooter and bike-sharing service that leverages IoT technology for user access, GPS tracking, and data analytics to improve urban mobility and user experience.\n\n7. **Lumos** - A smart cycling helmet that features integrated lights and turn signals to enhance visibility and safety, emphasizing the integration of technology in consumer wearables.\n\n8. **Figma** - While more B2B-focused, Figma has gained traction among consumers for its collaborative design capabilities. It allows users to design and prototype in real-time, revolutionizing the design process.\n\n9. **Calm** - A wellness app focusing on meditation, sleep, and relaxation, using advanced algorithms to personalize content for users and integrating various technological enhancements.\n\n10. **Gopuff** - A delivery startup that utilizes a vertically-integrated model using technology to streamline inventory management and logistics for rapid on-demand delivery of consumer goods.\n\nThese startups have been recognized for leveraging technology to create innovative solutions and improve consumer experiences across various industries.",
